1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
When the Sun and Moon align, tides soar to new heights.

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:07,200
But when they pull at right angles?

3
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:08,400
Tides calm down.

4
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:10,800
Welcome to the world of tides!

5
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:14,400
Spring tides—higher and stronger—occur during full and new moons.

6
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:20,000
Neap tides, on the other hand, show up during the first and last quarters.

7
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,600
They keep things moderate.

8
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:26,400
Understanding these cycles helps us predict coastal behaviors and marine life patterns.

9
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:27,200
Fascinating, right?

10
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:29,600
Want to dive deeper into science?

11
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:30,800
Hit that follow!

12
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:32,400
See you next time!
